1. *Snovi* su često tema umetničkih dela. (*Snovi* - Nouns, dreams are often the subject of artworks.)
2. Noćas sam imao *snove* o putovanju u Japan. (*Snove* - Noun, I had dreams about traveling to Japan last night.)
3. Ona *sniva* o svom venčanju već godinama. (*Sniva* - Verb, She has been dreaming about her wedding for years.)
4. Naši *snovi* su postali stvarnost. (*Snovi* - Noun, Our dreams have become a reality.)
5. Nemoj da pokušavaš da mi *snoviš* o nečemu što nije istina. (*Snoviš* - Verb, Don't try to dream up something that isn't true.)
6. *Snoveći* o letovanju na obali mora, osetio sam miris soli u vazduhu. (*Snoveći* - Verb, Dreaming about vacationing on the seaside, I smelled the salt in the air.)
7. *Snovima* je samo granica naša mašta. (*Snovima* - Noun, Dreams are only limited by our imagination.)
8. Oni su oduvek verovali da se *snovi* ostvaruju ako dovoljno verujete. (*Snovi* - Noun, They have always believed that dreams come true if you believe enough.)
9. U ovoj knjizi ima mnogo lepih *snova*. (*Snova* - Noun, There are many beautiful dreams in this book.)
10. Nije lako razlikovati *stvarnost* od *snova* kada se neispunjena želja često pretvara u imaginarnu situaciju. (*Snova* - Noun, It is not easy to distinguish reality from dreams when an unfulfilled desire often turns into an imaginary situation.)